## Exploratory data analysis and feature creation
### What did the exploratory analysis find and how did you add additional features?

During EDA we gained some insight about how features are distributed. We can clearly see that `season`, `holiday`, `workingday`, `weather` columns have discrete distribution which signifies the fact that they represnt categorical features so it may be better to tell AugoGluon that these are categorical features. Another obsrvation I made was that perhaps we can make our model work better if we extract year,month & day from `datetime` feature.

### How much better did your model preform after adding additional features and why do you think that is?


The `RMSE` score has dropped from 53.120597 to 35.884354 so that's about 32% improvement

## Hyper parameter tuning
### How much better did your model preform after trying different hyper parameters?

It slightly enhanced our public kaggle score by 3%

### If you were given more time with this dataset, where do you think you would spend more time?
I would try different initial hyperparameter optimizaion, increased the `time_limit` paramater or perhaps not enforce a time limit and try different settings for other parameters ,e.g. `num_stack_levels`, `num_bag_folds` , `num_bag_sets` and `autostack` as bagging tends to give better performance than HPO.
